.lightbox(ng-show='show')
  .modal
    p.lead(ng-show="poplib==1")
      span.capitalize {{name1}}&nbsp;
      | has just turned {{number | number}}, and only has a few more years to go before he 
      | retires from the Los Angeles Police Department. {{name2}} has just lost his {{relative}} when she was {{death}}, 
      | and doesn't care if he lives or dies. When they are paired together, {{name1}} has 
      | problems with {{name2}}'s suicidal attitude towards work, as they investigate a {{noun}} baron dubbed "{{nickname}}".
    p.lead(ng-show='poplib==2')
      | A teenage hacker finds himself framed for the theft of {{thingToSteal}} from a major corporation. 
      | Master hacker {{name1}}, aka {{codeName}}, aka {{codeName2}}, has been banned from touching a keyboard 
      | for {{number | number}} years after crashing over 1,500 {{company}} computers at the age of 11. Now keen to get back in 
      | front of a monitor, he finds himself in more trouble than ever.
    p.lead(ng-show='poplib==3')
      | When her {{relative}} is turned into a zombie and attacks her, Ana just manages to escape, 
      | only to realize her entire {{town}} neighborhood has been overrun by the walking dead. After being 
      | questioned by {{adjective}} {{job}} Kenneth, Ana joins him and a small group that gravitates 
      | to the {{place}} as a bastion of safety. Once they convince suspicious {{people}} that 
      | they are not contaminated, the group bands together to fight the undead hordes.
    p.lead(ng-show='poplib==4')
      | In this {{adjective}} adventure, {{adjective2}} phenomena surface around the globe. The skies ignite. 
      | Terror races through the world's {{place}}. As these extraordinary events unfold, it becomes increasingly clear 
      | that a force of incredible magnitude has arrived; its mission: {{mission}} over the Fourth of July weekend. 
      | The last hope to stop the destruction is an unlikely group of {{noun}} united by fate and unimaginable circumstances.
    p.lead(ng-show='poplib==5')
      | Against the advice of locals and police, {{name}} scours the eerie {{place}} 
      | surrounding Crystal Lake for his missing {{relative}}. But the {{adjective}} {{noun}} of an abandoned summer camp are 
      | not the only things he finds. {{adjective2}} killer Jason Voorhees lies in wait for a chance to use his 
      | razor-sharp {{noun2}} on {{name}} and the group of college students who have come to the forest to {{verb}}.
    p.lead(ng-show='poplib==6')
      | When their kingdom becomes trapped in perpetual winter, {{adjective}} Anna joins forces with 
      | {{job}} Kristoff and his {{animal}} sidekick to find Anna's sister, Snow Queen Elsa, 
      | and break her icy spell. Although their epic journey leads them to encounters with {{adjective3}} 
      | {{monster}}, a {{adjective2}} snowman, harsh conditions, and magic at every turn, Anna and 
      | Kristoff bravely push onward in a race to save their kingdom from winter's cold grip.
    button(ng-click="newLib()") Do Another
    button(ng-click="redoLib()") Redo This One
